[[File:Livingston-Greenwich-map.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Illustrated map]] '''Cartography''' is making [[map]]s. Cartography is part of [[geography]]. How people make maps is always changing. In the past, maps were drawn by hand, but today most printed maps are made using [[computer]]s. Someone who makes maps is called a cartographer.
Making a map can be as simple as drawing a direction on a napkin, or as complicated as showing a [[census]] of a whole country. Anyone can make a map, but there are people who spend their lives learning how to make complicated maps.
